description: Upgrade your hummus hit with the sweetness of roasted squash and an aromatic dukkah topping.
name: Roasted Butternut Squash Hummus with Dukkah Recipe | Woolworths

recipeInstructions.text: Pre-heat the oven to 200°C/180°C fan-forced and add the butternut chunks, garlic cloves and a tablespoon of olive oil to a roasting tin. Cover with foil and roast for 20 minutes, then remove the foil and roast for 10 more minutes until lightly caramelised.

Place the butternut squash, peeled garlic cloves, remaining oil, lemon juice and a pinch of zest, paprika, tahini, a teaspoon of date syrup and chickpeas (including liquid from the can) in a food processor and pulse to a chunky dip consistency.
Scoop the hummus into a bowl and serve with dukkah and a teaspoon of date syrup drizzled on top.
